<title type="html"><![CDATA[SMB: PPU memory?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3723&amp;p=28549#p28549"><![CDATA[
Super Mario Bros has 32K PRG (2 banks) and 8K CHR (1 bank).  If your ROM does not indicate it has CHR-ROM, your header is either bad, or your ROM is bad, or you're reading the header wrong.<br /><br />In any event... typically when games do not have any CHR-ROM, you give them 8K CHR-RAM at ppu$0000-1FFF<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Wed Nov 21, 2007 9:18 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
